  "text": "Trace how an LLVM optimization pass is registered in the pass pipeline and executed. Find all C++ source files in `llvm/llvm-project` that participate in the optimization pipeline lifecycle: 1. The file that defines the `PassBuilder` class and its method for building the default O2 optimization pipeline (look in `llvm/lib/Passes/`). 2. The file that defines the `PassManager` template class \u2014 the core pass execution engine (look in `llvm/include/llvm/IR/`). 3. The file that implements `PassBuilderPipelines` which assembles the default module/function simplification pipelines. 4. The file that registers all standard passes via `PassRegistry.def`. 5. For a concrete example, the file implementing `DeadStoreElimination` in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/`. Report the repo, file path, and key class or function name for each.",
